{"count": 41734, "next": "https://api.acmi.net.au/works/?page=1392", "previous": "https://api.acmi.net.au/works/?page=1390", "results": [{"id": 114182, "acmi_id": "B1006116", "title": "Godspeed Verticals", "title_zh_hans": "", "title_pa": "", "title_hi": "", "title_annotation": "", "title_annotation_zh_hans": "", "title_annotation_pa": "", "title_annotation_hi": "", "slug": "godspeed-verticals", "creator_credit": "Shaun Gladwell and Mark Larenzetto", "credit_line": "", "credit_line_zh_hans": "", "credit_line_pa": "", "credit_line_hi": "", "headline_credit": "Australia, 2004", "video_links": [], "record_type": "work", "type": "Artwork", "is_on_display": false, "last_on_display_place": "ACMI Screen Gallery", "last_on_display_date": "2004-09-12", "is_context_indigenous": false, "material_description": "Multi channel moving image", "unpublished": false, "external": false, "first_production_date": "2004-01-01T11:00:00+11:00", "commissioned": true, "public_domain": false, "external_references": [], "brief_description": "<p>A dual screen digital video installation, &#8220;Godspeed Verticals&#8221; explores BMX bicycle riding and skateboarding and its relations to and functions within the urban environment through the large scale projection of two sequences of actions skewed at 90 degree angles. Recorded in a deliberately anonymous and generic underground carpark and walkway and presented in slow motion, these sequences subtly reference visual cultural practices and spectatorship in an art historical context while engaged in a meditative study of contemporary activities of urban expression. In the first sequence, the camera follows a single BMX bicycle rider as they manoeuvre towards the darkened exit/entrance of a vast walkway, the bike and rider alike appearing to be pulled up and beyond the frame through the skewed presentation of the image. A loose translation of Caspar David Friedrich&#8217;s &#8216;Wanderer above the Sea of Fog&#8217; (1818), the image stages the sublime position of the lone character in Friedrich&#8217;s painting in its representation of the BMX bicycle rider&#8217;s spatial orientation in and interaction with the contemporary urban landscape. Sequence two presents an aerial view of skateboarders falling into a tiled wall, some alone and others grouped together, with subtle reflections in composition on the geometry of Abstract art and the distant framing of imagery and figures in Western religious artworks. A layered soundscape of the sounds derived from the focal environment accompanies the projections to produce a low volume ambience for the on screen movements.</p>", "constellations_primary": [], "constellations_other": [], "recommendations": [], "creator_credit_for_label": "<p>Shaun Gladwell and Mark Larenzetto</p>", "creator_credit_for_label_zh_hans": "", "creator_credit_for_label_pa": "", "creator_credit_for_label_hi": "", "headline_credit_for_label": "<p>Australia, 2004</p>", "headline_credit_for_label_zh_hans": "", "headline_credit_for_label_pa": "", "headline_credit_for_label_hi": "", "title_for_label_zh_hans": "", "title_for_label_pa": "", "title_for_label_hi": "", "title_for_label_override_zh_hans": "", "title_for_label_override_pa": "", "title_for_label_override_hi": "", "description_for_label_zh_hans": "", "description_for_label_pa": "", "description_for_label_hi": "", "description_for_label_override_zh_hans": "", "description_for_label_override_pa": "", "description_for_label_override_hi": "", "description_zh_hans": "", "description_pa": "", "description_hi": "", "description_override_zh_hans": "", "description_override_pa": "", "description_override_hi": "", "title_for_label": "<p>Godspeed verticals</p>", "description": "<p>A dual screen digital video installation, <i>Godspeed Verticals</i> explores BMX bicycle riding and skateboarding and its relations to and functions within the urban environment through the large scale projection of two sequences of actions skewed at 90 degree angles. Recorde